# WhatsApp survey open-text flows (tell-us-more vs vague followup)

## Two separate flows — never conflate them

| Flow | Trigger | Outbound text | Send path | Conv flags |
|------|---------|---------------|-----------|------------|
| **Tell-us-more** | Worst button on any scale step (`feeling_word`, `helpfulness`, `yes_no`, `rating`, `abc_choice`) when tell-us-more template is configured | System template body (customisable) | **Always local session text** — `_send_freeform_whatsapp` / never Meta HSM | `tell_us_more_pending`, `last_outbound_kind=tell_us_more` |
| **Vague auto-followup** | Poor/vague answer when tell-us-more branch is **disabled** | `"What was wrong with {topic}?"` (generated) | **Always local session text** — `_send_freeform_whatsapp` | `vague_followup_sent_at`, `awaiting_followup`, `last_outbound_kind=vague_auto_followup` |

They are **mutually exclusive** on the same poor answer: when tell-us-more is configured/enabled, vague evaluation is skipped (`tell_us_more_blocks_vague_followup`).

## Tell-us-more send rules

- Outbound must use **server session free-form text** (24h customer-service window), **not** Meta HSM.
- Admin **Meta sync: Local** (`sync_from_meta=false`) is correct for tell-us-more — means send from local server, not Meta template push.
- `active_for_survey=true` on the system template row is required for resolution.
- `payload_source` = `builder_tell_us_more_template`.
- Question dict: `source=builder_tell_us_more_template`, `node_key` starts with `builder_tell_`, `reply_type=long_text`, no buttons.
- Even if the linked DB template row has stale `step_role=rating` or BUTTONS, the in-memory branch question overrides — use `is_tell_us_more_branch_question()`.

## Vague followup send rules

- Not the tell-us-more template. Text is built by `survey_wa_vague_negative_followup_service`.
- Accepts text **or** voice (transcribed via DeepInfra/Whisper when enabled).
- Voice routing: `is_awaiting_vague_followup_reply(conv)` → `answer_context=followup`.

## Voice notes on open-text steps

- Rejection message `"Voice notes are only supported for comment-style questions"` must **not** appear on tell-us-more or vague-followup replies.
- Requires `.env`: `allow_voice_notes_for_open_text=true`, `transcribe_voice_notes=true`, and Celery worker running.

## Admin-disabled topics

- `admin_hidden_from_survey=true` on a template row must **never** auto re-enable until admin explicitly enables it again. See `wa-template-admin-disable.mdc`.
